post_text: Calling all Cardinals! Get your votes in. This is the last week to make a name suggestion for our District Cardinal! #IAmEC
shared_text:
East Cleveland City Schools
July 6 at 6:04 PM ·

A new day is emerging! ...along with a new Cardinal!

We're looking for a name for our new cardinal! Do you have the perfect idea? Help us pick a name by following the steps below:

PHASE 1 - July 6th - July 18th

1️⃣ Comment a name suggestion in the comments section on this post on any of our social media platforms.

OR

2️⃣ Like the comment of a name that has already been suggested.

(Only comments and likes on The District's social media pages will be counted)

PHASE 2 - July 27th - July 31st

The top 3️⃣ name suggestions will be voted on by you. The new name of our cardinal, along with the picture, will be revealed at the beginning of the 2020-2021 school year.

#WhyEC? #IAMEC

post_text:
Congratulations to the following Business Management students who are advancing to the Network For Teaching Entrepreneurship (NFTE) Chicago Region E2 Finals on Wednesday, May 20, 2020:

Jefferson A., Maya H. and Shakarah R., JeffCo Brushes, a hair styling tool that dispenses product

Thomas B., Photo-Genesis, a web directory for photographers

John D., Subtract, a service that allows artists to license or incorporate "beats" into their music

Due to CoVID-19, both events will be held online via Zoom* with students competing from Illinois, Ohio and Wisconsin.
The winner of the national competition this October has the chance to win up to $25,000 for their business.
text:
Congratulations to the following Business Management students who are advancing to the Network For Teaching Entrepreneurship (NFTE) Chicago Region E2 Finals on Wednesday, May 20, 2020:

Jefferson A., Maya H. and Shakarah R., JeffCo Brushes, a hair styling tool that dispenses product

Thomas B., Photo-Genesis, a web directory for photographers

John D., Subtract, a service that allows artists to license or incorporate "beats" into their music

Due to CoVID-19, both events will be held online via Zoom* with students competing from Illinois, Ohio and Wisconsin.
The winner of the national competition this October has the chance to win up to $25,000 for their business.
